If God was not loving, there would be no willingness for his son to suffer and die.

18:10.189 --> 18:12.632
But God is, of course, both just and loving.

18:12.712 --> 18:16.576
Therefore, his love is willing to meet the demands of his justice.

18:17.798 --> 18:25.266
Oh, and if you haven't caught the scandal and the beauty of that in this moment, do you notice that God does everything for us within himself?

18:25.826 --> 18:26.788
justice and love.

18:28.891 --> 18:35.783
Abact, to verse 23, and you, with the help of wicked men, put him to death by nailing him on a cross.

18:35.924 --> 18:46.622
Peter is speaking to a vast group which included many people that had watched Jesus' miracles, heard him talk, and also were involved in calling for his crucifixion.

18:46.682 --> 18:51.090
Yet, the implication spreads wider than this crowd.

18:51.810 --> 18:55.716
The Bible teaches that every human being is guilty of putting Jesus on the cross.

18:56.196 --> 19:01.905
In that very first Christian message, all people are called out and our condition is not downplayed at all.

19:03.627 --> 19:05.430
I love the next verse.

19:05.450 --> 19:21.714
All the statements, all the sentences, past be human leaders, all the decisions of the human courts, all that was carried out by Pilate and the Roman occupation, all the religious condemnation and wrong preaching and action is now rejected, reversed and rescinded.

19:22.882 --> 19:29.690
But God, I know there are memes on this all the time where someone says, but God and repeats it 20 times, but really, but God.

19:30.691 --> 19:40.802
But God raised Jesus from the dead, freeing Jesus from the agony of death because it was impossible for death to keep hold of Jesus.

19:42.524 --> 19:43.125
Let me just do this.

19:44.206 --> 19:47.670
This is physical resurrection, not resuscitation.

19:48.531 --> 19:51.634
This is physical resurrection, not zombification.

19:52.738 --> 19:56.304
This is physical resurrection, not we stole the body and we're hiding it.

19:57.045 --> 20:00.751
This is physical resurrection, not mass hysteria and mass hallucination.

20:01.632 --> 20:03.495
This is physical resurrection.

20:03.555 --> 20:06.680
This is not spiritual ghost stuff.

20:07.081 --> 20:08.423
This is not the walking dead.

20:09.385 --> 20:11.228
Resurrection is an all or nothing deal.

20:12.169 --> 20:13.311
You got to catch this again.

20:13.511 --> 20:20.082
Christians unashamedly root ourselves in history and declare it's not just myth.

20:20.578 --> 20:27.006
We don't run from history because we believe the resurrection is an actual, provable, accessible historical event.

20:27.487 --> 20:36.138
Our whole movement is based on the idea that Jesus was really here historically, was really killed historically, was really dead, really physically rose from the dead.

20:36.719 --> 20:43.347
And when I was reading this years ago, I didn't catch this till a bit later, but it is so awesome.

20:44.469 --> 20:48.594
See the word agony, it says up there, freeing him from the agony of death,

20:49.474 --> 20:53.818
The word agony in the original language means birth pains, like contractions.

20:54.679 --> 20:56.821
I mean, this will preach all day long.

20:57.922 --> 21:08.852
Basically, this is what is being declared death was in labor and could not hold back the delivery of Jesus, like all the things.

21:10.734 --> 21:14.898
At this point, there would have been great confusion in this Orthodox Jewish audience.

21:14.918 --> 21:16.860
They, of course, have been taught their whole lives.

21:17.440 --> 21:19.282
The Messiah would never suffer.

21:20.162 --> 21:24.466
The Messiah would show up and restore the grand political religious kingdom and win.

21:25.707 --> 21:36.758
Cleanse the temple, destroy all false priests, restore the priests that are right to the right position, restore Israel's national boundaries, destroy the Romans, restore the glory of David.

21:37.198 --> 21:49.330
And I'm not saying this to be political or be a jerk, but like when Trump started saying, let's make America great again, that's a great summary statement of what Orthodox Jews believed.

21:49.890 --> 21:52.332
He's gonna come and make Israel great again.

21:53.554 --> 22:08.369
So to hear that the Messiah, the guy who's gonna save us and destroy our enemies and burn all the garbage away and make us the epicenter of the universe, ethnically, politically, fill in the blank, is gonna suffer, as one person said, it's like saying, oh, I can fry ice.

22:09.810 --> 22:12.953
And then Peter comes along and says, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

22:12.973 --> 22:17.458
When did we as Jews start thinking this wasn't supposed to happen to the Messiah?

22:17.890 --> 22:26.910
David, our greatest king, the man after God's own heart, wrote all those psalms, the one that God's promise was his line in kingdom would never end and change the world.

22:27.351 --> 22:29.717
He predicted the suffering of the Messiah, right?

22:30.819 --> 22:34.107
I mean, have we not all read and memorize Psalm 16, he'd say to the audience?

22:35.049 --> 22:37.394
I saw the Lord, all was before me.

22:38.050 --> 22:40.693
Because he's at my right hand and I will not be shaken.

22:40.713 --> 22:42.595
Therefore my heart is glad and my tongue rejoices.

22:42.656 --> 22:44.458
My body will rest in hope.

22:44.478 --> 22:44.718
Why?

22:44.798 --> 22:45.319
Verse 27.

22:45.659 --> 22:48.823
Because you will not abandon me to the realm of the dead.

22:49.944 --> 22:52.207
You will not let your holy ones see decay.

22:53.188 --> 22:55.111
You have made it known to me the paths of life.

22:55.191 --> 22:57.393
You will fill me with joy in your presence.

22:57.453 --> 22:58.595
Peter's like, hold on, hold on.

22:58.675 --> 23:00.097
David wrote this.

23:00.237 --> 23:01.398
David was a prophet.

23:01.719 --> 23:02.780
David was a king.

23:02.820 --> 23:04.322
David was our best poet.

23:04.622 --> 23:05.924
David was the great warrior.

23:06.284 --> 23:07.826
And David's dead, right?

23:08.194 --> 23:09.616
I mean, we can all walk to his tomb.

23:09.636 --> 23:10.357
Want to do a tour?

23:10.937 --> 23:11.979
It's just down the street.

23:12.940 --> 23:17.946
And obviously, David speaking about someone else, David was abandoned by God to death.

23:18.066 --> 23:18.567
He's dead.

23:18.907 --> 23:23.092
And his body experienced rotten worms, just like the rest of us will, like he decayed.

23:24.374 --> 23:28.880
So the question is, who in his family line did this happen to?

23:30.161 --> 23:31.783
My fellow Israelites, 29.

23:31.883 --> 23:37.330
I can tell you confidently that our patriarch, David, died and was buried,

23:37.634 --> 23:45.830
and his tomb is here till his day, but he was a prophet and knew that God had promised him on oath that he would place one of his descendants on that throne.

23:46.251 --> 23:53.245
Seeing what was to come, he spoke of the resurrection of the Messiah, that he would not be abandoned to the realm of dead nor his body see decay.

23:54.327 --> 23:56.050
Jesus fits the pattern.

23:56.674 --> 23:58.296
He's the fulfillment of the prophecy.

23:58.436 --> 24:01.000
Jesus was dead, but was not abandoned to dead.

24:01.080 --> 24:03.403
Jesus died, but his body did not see decay.

24:03.804 --> 24:04.405
He's alive.

24:04.605 --> 24:06.447
He is in the line of David.

24:06.628 --> 24:08.130
He is the throne of David.

24:08.450 --> 24:09.952
This is what we all need to see.

24:10.473 --> 24:14.298
God, verse 32, has raised this Jesus to life.

24:14.699 --> 24:16.821
We are all witnesses of it.

24:18.083 --> 24:20.126
Day one, Peter says, this is real.

24:20.186 --> 24:21.768
This actually happened.

24:22.149 --> 24:23.190
This is not invented.

24:23.230 --> 24:26.034
This is not some grand conspiracy or a lie.

24:26.210 --> 24:27.332
This is not borrowed myth.

24:28.313 --> 24:30.797
And we hear that claim in 2023.

24:32.019 --> 24:34.043
And a lot of us as modern people go, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

24:34.063 --> 24:35.485
John, come on.

24:35.505 --> 24:36.487
Come on, come on, come on.

24:36.507 --> 24:36.907
It's 2023.

24:37.729 --> 24:40.433
You know, they didn't have iPhones and they didn't have the internet.

24:41.775 --> 24:44.720
And they didn't have psychology and science and forensics.

24:44.740 --> 24:45.842
And so, you know, like,

24:46.498 --> 24:50.605
Ancient people are dumb and stupid and gullible, and they just believe any sort of myth and light.

24:50.625 --> 24:51.066
Stop it.

24:51.207 --> 24:52.549
That's not true, everyone.

24:52.769 --> 24:54.372
Let's all grow up in 2023.

24:54.412 --> 25:01.165
Talk to any historian at any university with their salt, and they will tell you ancient people are not stupid.

25:01.185 --> 25:03.048
Actually, ancient people are quite smart.

25:04.290 --> 25:06.695
This is what they call chronological snobbery.

25:08.738 --> 25:10.802
Tim Keller was reflecting on why he

25:11.298 --> 25:15.983
as a person and then as a leader and intellect and pastor, believe this was true.

25:16.183 --> 25:20.568
And one of the things he said, he says, look, he says, I read another book that really helped me.

25:20.588 --> 25:27.095
And he said, in his landmark book, Jesus and the eyewitnesses, a guy named Richard Buckingham, which by the way, is an incredible book.

25:27.876 --> 25:40.210
Marshall, so much historical evidence to demonstrate that the time the gospels were being written, Matthew, Mark, Luke, John, there were numerous well-known living eyewitnesses to Jesus' teaching and life events.

25:40.738 --> 25:42.019
They committed them to memory.

25:42.059 --> 25:45.222
They remained active in public and in the church throughout their lifetime.

25:45.523 --> 25:49.847
And they served as ongoing sources and guarantors of truth of those accounts.

25:50.127 --> 26:03.280
And he shows as a historian how in the gospels, even themselves, the gospel writers specifically name multiple eyewitnesses to assure the readers of the accounts authority and authenticity.

26:03.320 --> 26:09.746
In other words, if you wanted to invent a huge lie, you wouldn't name people that were all still living, that you could go interview.

26:09.890 --> 26:12.032
But they do it all the time, again and again and again.

26:12.353 --> 26:20.861
And the gospels weren't written 100, 200, 300 years later, like some wild scholars want to say, we're real close to the original moment.

26:20.881 --> 26:21.602
Peter keeps preaching.

26:23.024 --> 26:26.828
Jesus is exalted to the right hand of God.

26:28.249 --> 26:35.396
Jesus has received from the Father, that's I am, that's Yahweh, that's Elohim, that's the God of Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob.

26:36.417 --> 26:36.978
Jesus

26:37.218 --> 26:41.485
from the Father has received the promise Holy Spirit and has poured out what you now see in here.

26:42.386 --> 26:45.371
This is like, oh man, I can't even preach this well.

26:45.411 --> 26:46.473
The scandal of this.

26:47.034 --> 26:54.866
Jesus, the carpenter's son from Nazareth, who some people are like, we're not even sure what Mary's deal with it is.

26:55.426 --> 26:57.088
is now at the right hand of God.

26:57.108 --> 26:58.169
We talked about this last week.

26:58.509 --> 27:01.752
The right hand in the Bible is the place of all authority, all power.

27:02.033 --> 27:09.941
So when a king extended his right hand or the scepter, it could be life, death, blessing, war.

27:10.361 --> 27:13.564
It's the place and sign of ultimate decision.

27:14.926 --> 27:23.314
And Peter, a Galilean fisherman with his thick backwater accent that everyone dismissed, is now declaring that Jesus

27:24.034 --> 27:35.325
who had been executed, by the way, by the Romans 53 days earlier, is now sitting at God's right hand and has supremacy over the whole universe.

27:35.425 --> 27:36.386
Are you joking me?

27:37.307 --> 27:45.315
Oh, and oh, by the way, and Jesus has been given the Holy Spirit and Jesus is the one pouring out the Holy Spirit in this crazy moment.

27:47.017 --> 27:48.038
Then the implication comes home.

27:48.879 --> 27:50.941
Therefore, let all of Israel be assured of this.

27:51.421 --> 27:52.082
God

27:52.386 --> 27:57.054
made this Jesus whom you all crucified both Lord and Christ.

27:57.215 --> 27:58.597
Okay, here it is.

27:58.617 --> 28:01.462
This is the first confession of our faith.

28:02.284 --> 28:04.989
Jesus Christ is Lord.

28:06.151 --> 28:08.976
Jesus Christ is Lord.

28:10.399 --> 28:14.185
Remember that quote back from Joel 2, that Peter refers to, it's in verse 21.

28:14.747 --> 28:16.690
Everyone who calls on the name of the Lord will be saved.

28:17.570 --> 28:24.460
Years ago, when I was thinking through this passage, I found this incredible quotation by a guy named David Gooding, and he said, it's so good.

28:25.081 --> 28:26.323
They murdered God's son.

28:26.343 --> 28:28.786
He offered them his spirit.

28:29.587 --> 28:32.271
They crucified the second person of the eternity.

28:32.932 --> 28:33.994
He offered them the third.

28:34.795 --> 28:38.721
They threw God's son out of the vineyard in hope of inheriting the vineyard themselves.

28:39.442 --> 28:45.170
He now is inviting them to receive God's spirit, not just in their vineyard, but actually in their very hearts.

28:46.594 --> 28:47.916
That's why I got it so incredible.

28:49.117 --> 28:51.740
Well, in this moment, of course, the words hung in the air.

28:51.800 --> 28:53.302
What will happen next?

28:53.602 --> 29:00.550
Mob violence, dragging now Peter and others in front of the Sanhedrin in another call for either stoning to death or crucifixion.

29:00.570 --> 29:01.411
Would they walk away?

29:01.472 --> 29:02.393
Would they be dismissed?

29:02.413 --> 29:03.013
Yeah.

29:03.033 --> 29:04.555
Too many tequila shots, boys.

29:04.615 --> 29:05.817
Like, what is it going to be?

29:05.857 --> 29:06.758
Will it be accepted?

29:07.959 --> 29:10.242
Would holy fire start breaking out across this crowd?

29:11.263 --> 29:13.746
Well, when the people heard this, they were cut to their hearts.

29:13.922 --> 29:16.385
And they said to Peter and the other apostles, brothers, what shall we do?

29:16.465 --> 29:17.866
Now, cut to the heart.

29:18.167 --> 29:19.989
Some of you started singing some song from the 80s.

29:20.049 --> 29:20.589
Come on back.

29:21.811 --> 29:23.833
When you get cut, it's interesting.

29:24.173 --> 29:25.194
I got cut yesterday.

29:25.234 --> 29:26.556
I didn't do this for the sermon, by the way.

29:26.896 --> 29:29.819
A glass broke and I was picking up glass and a sink and it cut me.

29:31.301 --> 29:33.884
Though it's small, when you get cut, you feel it.

29:35.766 --> 29:37.367
Now, this is what they're feeling though.

29:37.488 --> 29:39.730
Can I beg everyone's attention, please?

29:41.122 --> 29:43.905
No matter where you are in the world, this, this matters.

29:44.486 --> 29:48.812
They're not just feeling as one person said anxiety or an awareness.

29:48.932 --> 29:49.612
I don't feel right.

29:49.653 --> 29:50.474
Something's wrong here.

29:51.595 --> 29:55.239
They're actually looking in the near and they now know they're complicit.

29:56.381 --> 29:57.042
They're guilt.

29:58.183 --> 30:00.626
I have personally done something wrong.

30:01.948 --> 30:02.709
You think about it.

30:04.331 --> 30:10.258
They suddenly realized that they have actually murdered, killed, executed the one they've been waiting for.

30:11.074 --> 30:13.577
And the only person who can forgive sins is Him.

30:14.959 --> 30:16.060
So who do you turn to now?

30:17.361 --> 30:19.364
Or are you just waiting to be judged on judgment date?

30:20.125 --> 30:22.167
There is no other court to go to.

30:25.110 --> 30:29.175
See, in this moment, they realized.

30:30.316 --> 30:35.122
Hopefully in this moment, some of you are realizing we are so far from God.

30:36.066 --> 30:39.290
There is nothing we can do to match his law, his holiness.

30:39.550 --> 30:49.961
When we actually see our sin, when we see that every one of us is complicit in God, God, the son's murder, our sickness, our separation, we say, is there anyone who's even willing to help?

30:51.963 --> 30:53.886
Peter replied, repent.

30:55.227 --> 30:56.088
Be baptized.

30:56.108 --> 31:01.794
Every one of you in the name of Jesus Christ for the forgiveness of your sins and you will receive the gift of the Holy Spirit.

31:02.215 --> 31:03.316
How do we get out of this mess?

31:03.376 --> 31:03.917
We repent.

31:04.257 --> 31:05.298
What does repent mean?

31:05.762 --> 31:08.425
Repent is not just, oh, I feel anxiety that I've done something bad.

31:08.806 --> 31:10.548
Repentance is, I am a sinner.

31:10.568 --> 31:12.631
I have assaulted the Holy God.

31:13.171 --> 31:18.618
I am turning from that, admitting my sin, and saying I'm guilty and asking for forgiveness.

31:18.878 --> 31:19.679
I'm doing a 180.

31:21.141 --> 31:26.768
Faith is that you put your trust in something or someone else to do the covering.

31:28.330 --> 31:30.152
It's one thing to know that Jesus existed.

31:31.134 --> 31:34.578
It's another thing to personally ask Jesus to cover what you've done.

31:35.362 --> 31:37.484
Faith is not blind leaping in the dark.

31:38.265 --> 31:40.928
Faith is informed trust in a person you get to know.

31:41.829 --> 31:43.992
Repentance, faith, and baptism.

31:44.412 --> 31:48.877
Baptism is the outward symbol of the inward decision, like I say all the time.

31:49.418 --> 31:50.820
It's like putting on a wedding ring.

31:51.380 --> 31:52.522
This doesn't make you married.

31:52.822 --> 31:53.903
It's the public declaration.

31:54.023 --> 31:54.804
You are married.

31:55.245 --> 32:03.314
See, when you repent, this is so cool, and you put your faith in Jesus alone, he gives you, he baptizes you in the spirit.

32:03.426 --> 32:07.772
Baptism in the Spirit is not a secondary thing that you get when you pray lots.

32:07.853 --> 32:11.177
It happens to every Christian on earth that says yes to Jesus.

32:11.558 --> 32:14.362
You are sealed by the Spirit at that moment.

32:15.524 --> 32:23.556
Peter keeps going, verse 39, the promise is for you and for your children and even for all those people who are far off, for all whom the Lord God will call.

32:23.636 --> 32:29.304
And with many other words, he warned them and pleaded with them, save yourself from this corrupt generation.

32:30.326 --> 32:33.330
I read this week again, I was like, wow, wow, wow.

32:33.570 --> 32:34.771
I gotta just pause here.

32:35.072 --> 32:36.393
Corrupt generation, really?

32:36.413 --> 32:41.499
I mean, Peter's speaking in the middle of the center of the world, Jerusalem, right?

32:41.819 --> 32:50.929
During a religious gathering full of really good, nice people who gave up time and money to actually come and worship the true living God, and they're doing all these good religious acts.

32:51.309 --> 32:53.512
And Peter says, you're all corrupt.

32:55.394 --> 32:58.016
Being religious, being sincere doesn't save you.

32:58.617 --> 33:01.360
It's not what you do, it's who you know that makes the difference.

33:02.842 --> 33:03.122
Well,

33:04.098 --> 33:06.322
Those who accepted, and those means not all.

33:06.944 --> 33:08.967
Those that accepted Peter's message were baptized.

33:08.988 --> 33:10.951
3,000 added to their number that day.

33:11.072 --> 33:16.582
In one day, when the church was born with an hour, 3,000 people from the whole known world joined.

33:16.963 --> 33:20.530
And just so no one misunderstands, after they repented,

33:20.610 --> 33:26.777
after they believed Jesus was a Messiah, after they believed he was the Son of God, after they actually said, Jesus, would you forgive me?

33:26.957 --> 33:31.983
After they became disciples or Christians, then they got baptized.

33:32.063 --> 33:33.524
Baptism does not save you.

33:33.925 --> 33:36.147
It is evidence of something that's already happened.

33:36.508 --> 33:38.570
They're not trusting in a new moral system.

33:38.870 --> 33:40.572
They're not trusting in a moral code.

33:40.792 --> 33:42.594
They're not trusting in the religious actions.

33:42.875 --> 33:44.897
They're trusting in a loving, living person.

33:44.977 --> 33:49.522
Jesus, the Son of God, the Son of man, the Lord, who came to seek and saved the lost.

33:51.330 --> 33:52.451
Why does this sermon matter?

33:52.591 --> 33:53.292
Okay, here it is.

33:53.732 --> 33:53.953
Ready?

33:54.413 --> 33:55.774
This is the summary of our faith.

33:56.955 --> 33:59.638
For the seekers among us, the skeptics among us, for all of us.

34:00.659 --> 34:02.481
This is it, spelled out, clear as day.

34:02.661 --> 34:04.062
Jesus sums up the Old Testament.

34:04.863 --> 34:06.485
He's the fulfillment of the Jewish faith.

34:07.305 --> 34:09.988
Jesus was a real man whose life was marked by miracles.

34:10.709 --> 34:12.390
Jesus was actually crucified.

34:13.031 --> 34:14.913
It was God's plan all along to do this.

34:15.694 --> 34:18.296
Jesus really was physically risen from the dead.

34:19.137 --> 34:20.338
Jesus is king.

34:20.706 --> 34:22.228
Jesus is reigning right now.

34:22.929 --> 34:24.370
This is Jesus' world.

34:25.231 --> 34:26.413
All of us are in sin.

34:26.453 --> 34:28.615
Every human being is corrupt.

34:29.456 --> 34:31.419
Even the most religious person is guilty.

34:32.220 --> 34:33.581
All humans need a Savior.

34:34.482 --> 34:37.466
Jesus is not just a man, though he is a man.

34:37.526 --> 34:39.368
He is also God in flesh.

34:40.129 --> 34:45.335
If you accept Jesus, have faith in Jesus, you get the greatest gift that's the Holy Spirit.

34:45.796 --> 34:47.538
You'll be forgiven of your sins.

34:47.746 --> 34:51.711
You get to join God's real family and movement, no matter your history or background.

34:52.292 --> 34:53.834
Resurrection is guaranteed.

34:54.514 --> 35:03.646
God who is holy, God who is love, God is not silent, and this God who is loving and holy and does not remain silent has reached out.

35:03.966 --> 35:07.470
Anyone who calls on the name of the Lord will be saved.

35:07.731 --> 35:10.875
That's not just good news, that's not just some news, that's the news.

35:10.935 --> 35:13.037
That's the best news.

35:15.060 --> 35:16.882
We don't shrink, by the way,

35:18.178 --> 35:20.341
from the resurrection being the place of validation.

35:21.663 --> 35:24.347
And we do believe in exclusive claims and truth.

35:24.367 --> 35:33.140
Yes, all of us live in this postmodern, multicultural, pluralistic moment that teaches us truth is subjective, or many of us deny the absolute understanding of truth.

35:33.200 --> 35:37.306
Most believe truth, of course, is just discovered through experience or culture.

35:37.627 --> 35:40.311
It's my truth for a time, but the Christian faith says no.

35:41.633 --> 35:45.298
We're not going to skirt around the issue of sin, spiritual corruption and death.

35:45.730 --> 35:53.620
Peter's message is that we all actually know something is wrong and something is wrong in the human family, but spiritual anxiety is not enough.

35:53.900 --> 35:56.083
The feeling of being off is not enough.

35:56.643 --> 35:59.787
We have to admit, I'm guilty and I repent.

36:01.069 --> 36:14.866
We as Christians are pessimistic about human nature, but we're incredibly excited, blown away, hopeful about the love and grace of God by the Holy Spirit that shows us Jesus, that can transform you from the inside out.

36:15.010 --> 36:21.378
The Spirit of God can take the most hostile, barren desert-like life and make it bloom.

36:23.180 --> 36:33.293
For you who have not yet met Jesus, or you are cultural Christians, or you're from another faith or spiritual, I found this really intriguing, punchy thought from the 70s.

36:33.874 --> 36:36.337
One person said, the question is not, shall I repent?

36:39.220 --> 36:40.362
For that is beyond doubt.

36:41.523 --> 36:43.666
The question is, shall I repent now?

36:44.386 --> 36:50.876
when it may save me, or will I put off my repentance to eternity when my repentance will then become punishment."

36:54.442 --> 36:56.445
Here's what Paul wrote later.

36:56.465 --> 37:00.011
He who killed Christians and attacked us and then became one of us.

37:01.453 --> 37:12.370
Romans 10 and 9, this is to all of you who have not yet said, yes, if you declare with your mouth Jesus is Lord, and you believe in your heart God raised Jesus from the dead, you will be saved.

37:13.698 --> 37:18.604
Just like Peter preached 2000 years ago, I'm now preaching now with the same spirit he had.

37:20.527 --> 37:26.394
And the same Holy Spirit that was speaking to that crowd then is speaking to this crowd now, to you now.

37:27.055 --> 37:34.745
If you have never accepted Jesus, if you've never trusted in Jesus for salvation, eternal life, and all that, this is what you need to do right now.

37:34.785 --> 37:41.554
Be cut to the heart, admit your guilty say, Dear Lord Jesus, pray this out loud in your heart, but just say, Dear Lord Jesus, I know I'm a sinner.

37:42.754 --> 37:44.155
I ask for your forgiveness.

37:45.396 --> 37:47.098
I believe you died for my sins.

37:48.700 --> 37:50.141
I believe you rose from the dead.

37:51.122 --> 37:54.245
I turn from running my own life, and now I ask you to run it.

37:55.426 --> 37:56.627
Be the Lord of my life.

37:58.128 --> 38:00.671
I invite you to come into my heart and my life.

38:01.832 --> 38:04.935
I trust and follow you as Lord and Savior.

38:05.916 --> 38:08.899
This is what I pray in Jesus' name.

38:10.860 --> 38:12.562
And we all said, amen.

38:13.954 --> 38:24.447
Last thought, Peter knows our tendency of being embarrassed or wanting to not deny what is true.

38:24.888 --> 38:26.710
If anyone knows it, Peter knows it.

38:28.272 --> 38:35.661
The Spirit of God reminds you as a Christian if you're hearing this message today or days or months or decades later, don't back down He cries.

38:36.382 --> 38:43.090
Don't turn, don't be embarrassed, don't be relunked, don't be humiliated into silence or compromise.

38:44.290 --> 38:45.692
Do not be ashamed of the gospel.

38:46.413 --> 38:53.702
The gospel is the life, the death, and the physical resurrection of Jesus and the offering of forgiveness of sins alone.

38:54.643 --> 39:01.752
Boldly proclaim the good news, because if Peter could be transformed by Jesus and be used, so can you.

39:02.433 --> 39:03.194
So can all of us.

39:03.975 --> 39:05.277
Father and Son, send the Spirit.

39:05.877 --> 39:07.079
Open people's eyes to Jesus.

39:07.520 --> 39:08.941
Father and Son, send the Spirit.

39:09.402 --> 39:10.924
Help us not to be ashamed of the gospel.

39:11.024 --> 39:12.626
Father and Son, send the Spirit.

39:12.834 --> 39:17.827
Help us and give us opportunities to speak, to point, to encourage people to meet Christ.

39:17.867 --> 39:18.869
We pray this as a church.

39:19.170 --> 39:21.937
We all said in Jesus' name, amen.

39:22.318 --> 39:23.762
We'll see you next week.

